President Donald Trump welcomed Foxconn to the White House to announce a technology manufacturing initiative that will bring thousands of jobs and billions of dollars in investments to America. Foxconn, a world leader in manufacturing for computers, communications, and consumer electronics, will build a state-of-the-art manufacturing facility for LCD panel products in southern Wisconsin, representing a major advancement in regaining America's place in advanced electronics manufacturing. The $10 billion investment is expected to create thousands of new American jobs and demonstrates that America's capabilities are limitless. The new Foxconn plant has the potential to be one of the largest non-energy manufacturing job creators in modern US history.